Loop through the values, each it is larger than the previous peak value, update the peak value and also the index. Return the index after completing.

```
public class Solution {
    public static int peakIndexInMountainArray(int[] arr) {
        int peakValue = 0;
        int peakIndex = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; arr.length; i++) {
            int value = arr[i];
            if (value &gt; peakValue) {
                peakValue = value;
                peakIndex = i;
            }
        }
        return peakIndex;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(&quot;Set 1: &quot; + peakIndexInMountainArray(new int[]{0,1,2}));
        System.out.println(&quot;Set 2: &quot; + peakIndexInMountainArray(new int[]{0,1,0}));
        System.out.println(&quot;Set 3: &quot; + peakIndexInMountainArray(new int[]{0,2,1,0}));
